'Nucs', or 'Nucleus Colonies', are small honey bee colonies created from larger
colonies. The term refers both to the smaller size box and the colony of
honeybees within it. The name is derived from the fact that a nuc hive is
centered around a queen - the nucleus of the honey bee colony.
